            "id": "4459964",
            "title": "Crude oil tanker company DHT Holdings to acquire a 2018 built VLCC",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Crude oil tanker company DHT Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DHT\" title=\"DHT Holdings, Inc.\">DHT</a></span>) has agreed to acquire a VLCC built in 2018 at Hyundai Heavy Industries (HHI), for $107 million, it <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20142309-dht-holdings-inc-announces-agreement-to-acquire-a-2018-built-vlcc\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"said\">said</a> on Thursday.</li>\n<li>The vessel is scheduled to be delivered towards the end of the third quarter of 2025.</li>\n<li>The acquisition will be financed through the company’s available liquidity and projected mortgage debt.</li>\n<li>The vessel was built to a high specification by its current owner and is fitted with an exhaust gas cleaning system.</li>\n<li>The acquisition will improve DHT’s age profile and will further improve the DHT fleet’s efficiency metrics. </li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
