            "id": "4459955",
            "title": "Japan’s core inflation accelerates for the third straight month to 3.7%",
            "description": "<html><body><p>Japan's core inflation, which excludes fresh food but includes energy, accelerated for the third consecutive month to 3.7% from 3.5% in April, the highest since January 2023. The figure also topped market expectations of a 3.6% increase.</p>\n<p>Monthly, the CPI rose 0.3%, after a 0.1% gain in April.</p>\n<p>Japan's annual inflation rate edged down to 3.5% in May 2025 from 3.6% in the previous two months, marking the lowest level since November. </p>\n<p>Food prices in Japan rose 6.5% year-on-year in May 2025, matching April’s pace while remaining at the slowest increase since December. </p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NKY:IND#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">Nikkei 225 Index</a> rose 0.4% to above 38,600 on Friday, recouping some losses from the previous session, as investors digested Japan’s latest inflation figures. The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USD:JPY#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">Japanese yen</a> strengthened toward 145 per dollar on Friday, recovering some of its recent losses.</p>\n<h2>More on Japan</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4438674-japans-manufacturing-pmi-revised-upward-to-487-in-april\">Japan's manufacturing PMI revised upward to 48.7 in April</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4452761-japan-to-spend-388-billion-on-relief-measures-for-us-tariff-impact\">Japan to spend ¥388 billion on relief measures for U.S. tariff impact</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4429976-japan-producer-prices-rise-more-than-expected-to-42-in-march\">Japan producer prices rise more than expected to 4.2% in March</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4427230-japan-s-unemployment-rate-unexpectedly-drops-to-2_4-percent-in-february\">Japan’s unemployment rate unexpectedly drops to 2.4% in February</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4426744-japans-feb-industrial-production-exceeds-expectations-retail-sales-fall-short-of-forecasts\">Japan's Feb industrial production exceeds expectations, retail sales fall short of forecasts</a></li>\n</ul></body></html>",
